"'''Rude Boy'''" is a song by [[Barbadian people|Barbadian]] recording artist [[Rihanna]], taken from her fourth studio album, ''[[Rated R (Rihanna album)|Rated R]]'' (2009). The song was released as the third single from the album on February 19, 2010 through [[The Island Def Jam Music Group|Def Jam]]. It was written by [[Stargate (production team)|Mikkel S. Eriksen, Tor Erik Hermansen]], [[Ester Dean]], [[Makeba Riddick]], [[Rob Swire]] and Rihanna, with production completed by Eriksen and Hermansen (under their production name [[Stargate (production team)|StarGate]]) and Swire. "Rude Boy" is an [[up-tempo]] song which draws heavy influence from [[dancehall]], [[Pop music|pop]] and [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]. 

"Rude Boy" received mixed to positive reviews from critics, with some commenting that it is the highlight of the album, whilst others criticized Rihanna's "monotone" and "icy" vocal performance. The song debuted on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] at number sixty-four, and peaked at number one in its fourth week for five consecutive weeks, giving Rihanna her sixth number one song on the chart. The song also topped the US [[Mainstream Top 40 (Pop Songs)|Pop Songs]] and [[Hot Dance Club Songs|Dance/Club Play Songs]] charts. "Rude Boy" was a commercial success internationally, peaking at number one in Australia and attained top five positions in Germany, Hungary, Ireland, New Zealand, Norway, Poland, Slovakia and the United Kingdom.

The song's accompanying music video was directed by [[Melina Matsoukas]] and was shot in January 2010 in [[Hollywood, Los Angeles, California]]. The video relied heavily on the use of "[[greenscreen]]" and featured an array of props, such as a stuffed lion and zebra. The song was performed for the first time at the  Pepsi Super Bowl Fan Jam in South Beach, Miami, as well as on ''[[The Ellen Degeneres Show]]'' and ''[[Alan Carr: Chatty Man]]''. The song was also featured on both the [[Last Girl on Earth Tour]] and the current [[Loud Tour]]. 

==Background and composition==
